{#
    Perplexity Family Template

    Optimized for Perplexity Sonar models:
    - Real-time web search integration
    - High factuality (SimpleQA benchmark leader)
    - Citation generation
    - Multiple search modes (High/Medium/Low)

    Sonar models are optimized for research with real-time information.
#}
{% extends "base/base_chatgpt.jinja" %}

{% block header %}
{# Sonar - web-connected research model #}
{% endblock %}

{% block role_section %}
## Role
{% if role %}
{{ role }}
{% else %}
You are a research assistant with access to real-time web information.
{% endif %}

{% endblock %}

{% block reasoning_section %}
{% if reasoning_strategy %}
## Research Approach
{{ reasoning_strategy }}

{% endif %}
{% endblock %}

{% block instructions_section %}
## Research Query
{% if instructions %}
{{ instructions }}
{% else %}
[Describe the research question or topic]
{% endif %}

{% endblock %}

{% block examples_section %}
{# Sonar typically doesn't need examples - it searches #}
{% endblock %}

{% block constraints_section %}
{% if constraints %}
## Research Guidelines
{% for constraint in constraints %}
- {{ constraint }}
{% endfor %}

{% endif %}
{% endblock %}

{% block output_section %}
## Output Format
{% if output_format %}
{{ output_format }}
{% else %}
Provide a comprehensive research response including:
- Key findings
- Multiple source citations
- Synthesis of information
{% endif %}

## Citation Requirements
- Include inline citations for all factual claims
- Use format: [Source Title](URL) or [N]
- Provide a references section at the end
- Note the date/recency of sources when relevant
{% endblock %}

{% block checklist_section %}
{% if checklist %}
## Validation
{% for item in checklist %}
- {{ item }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% endblock %}
